# Spark Estate UI Philosophy™

**Authority:** `docs/estate/ESTATE_ARCHITECTURAL_AUTHORITY.md` — Constitution · Experience Guide · Bible (binding)  
**Extended:** `docs/SPARK_ESTATE_UI_PHILOSOPHY.md` — Bible Ch 8 wins on conflict

**Wins over:** feature-first panels, room headers, invitation grids, instructional overlays in older templates.

## Photograph Test

> Could this frame hang on a wall — and still feel like somewhere you would want to live?

## Three layers only

1. **Scene** — estate image/video, full bleed, always the hero (≥70% visual weight)
2. **Float** — frosted conversation panel centered over scene ([Spec 109](../docs/SPARK_FROSTED_CONVERSATION_WORKSPACE_FRAMEWORK.md))
3. **Object** — physical affordance in-scene (book, folio, drawer) — Destination Rooms only

## Non-negotiables

- Estate image is **always** the hero — never a background behind a dashboard
- Chat **floats** over the scene — no split chat + tools columns
- **Guidebook** = physical book (pages, cover, close) — never help-center sidebar
- **No** dashboards · software panels · unnecessary buttons · room labels · instructional overlays

## Forbidden

Sidebars · top app bars · workspace placeholders as arrival · “Welcome to…” tours · room title chrome · emoji feature grids · KPI tiles · breadcrumbs · `No data found` empty tables · white canvas gutters

## Allowed (sparingly)

Full-bleed scene · frosted chat · mic/send · one primary action · folded map (corner) · object-layer UI in Destinations · diegetic text **in artwork only** · recessive ambience toggle

## Button rule

**Necessity Test:** Would this control exist if you were standing in the real room?

## Before shipping Estate UI

- [ ] Photograph Test passes?
- [ ] Scene hero, chat floats, no labels/overlays?
- [ ] Every button necessary?
- [ ] Guidebook/objects feel physical?
- [ ] Shari test — not software copy?

**Any no → not shippable.**

## Build test

Would someone want to **stay** here — not just get something done? See `docs/estate/Living in Spark Estate.md`.
